    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="909"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d909">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.001H87/6.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hurst</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Barcelona</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-09-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1914-09-16T00:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>
                        <hi rend="italic">; received September 17, 1914.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ex-President Huerta, with family and suite including five Mexican generals, now
                    in Barcelona. Son of General Zelaya of Nicaragua also here. General Porfirio
                    Diaz stated to have arrived incognito but left some time ago.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurst</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
